# SANKO VISION DEMO — PHASE 3: Practitioner View

## Context
Phases 1-2 built the project, data layer, shell, and Home view. Now build the Practitioner view — this is the most complex view with sidebar navigation and multiple sub-views.

## What to build
Create src/views/PractitionerView.jsx and import it into App.jsx, replacing the practitioner placeholder.

## Architecture
PractitionerView has internal state managing which sub-view is shown in the main content area. The sidebar is always visible on the left.

```jsx
const [subView, setSubView] = useState('dashboard');
const [selectedFormulation, setSelectedFormulation] = useState(null);
const [selectedPatient, setSelectedPatient] = useState(null);
```

When selectedFormulation is set, show FormulationDetail instead of the current sub-view.
When selectedPatient is set, show PatientTimeline instead of the current sub-view.

## Layout
Use CSS grid: `grid-template-columns: 260px 1fr` with 20px gap. Max-width 1200px, centered, padding 24px.

On mobile (< 900px), stack vertically.

